AUDIO: 'best open-source model you can use right now, so definitely give it a try. Next up, this AI is super useful. It\'s called High Stream and this basically speeds up your video generations using Alibaba\'s'

[20:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'one by like over a hundred times. So, if you\'ve been like generating AI videos, you\'ve probably heard of Alibaba 1, which is currently the best open-source video generator out there, but it\'s'

[21:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'still very slow for most consumer GPUs. Like, for me, it takes at least 5 minutes to generate a 5-second clip. But high stream speeds up the generation by like up to 107 times, which is crazy. So'

[21:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a generation that would usually take five minutes for me could be done in like 2 or 3 seconds. Now, how does this work? Here basically speeds up your generation by cutting out a lot of'

[21:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'repeated work or redundancies. So when you\'re generating a video, there\'s a lot of temporal redundancies. So in simple terms, what high stream does is it works in chunks instead of looking at all the'

[21:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'frames so far, which gets slower as the video grows, but it always uses the first frame as like the anchor, so that the overall picture stays consistent. And then it also takes a few recent'

[22:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'nearby frames for motion context. So they also call this an anchor guided sliding window. And this keeps the amount of attention and memory the model uses fixed and small as the video gets longer. They also use spatial'

[22:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'compression which works like this. Instead of doing everything at full size right away, Highream first builds a rough version of the video at low resolution and then it refineses that rough version into a higher resolution'

[22:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'using some stored features from the earlier step. So it\'s kind of like upscaling the video as it generates it. And so afterwards, you get a model that\'s like 107 times faster than just the regular 1 2.1 generation. Plus, the'

[22:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'quality is actually preferred compared to all these other acceleration methods, as well as compared with the original 12.1 without any acceleration as well as another video model called LTX. In fact,'

[22:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
